    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>The action or state of being officially consigned to the custody of others or to confinement. A common example is when a person is committed to a psychiatric hospital due to their being judged a danger to themselves or others.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
